Maintainer: Ross J. Reedstrom <reedstrm@cnx.org>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>> 4.0.0)
Standards-Version: 3.6.1.0

Package: connexions-cnxml-common
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, docbook-xsl
Description: Connexions Markup Language common files (stylesheets)
 Connexions Markup Language (CNXML), an XML application for
 marking up educational texts. It is designed for use in the
 Connexions Project, but we are making it generally
 available in the hopes that others may find it useful.
 CNXML marks up the structure and semantic content of a
 document and encourages the separation of content from
 presentation.
 .
 Author:  The Connexions Language Team <cnxml@cnx.org>
 .
 Homepage: http://cnx.org/technology/cnxml/

